  <brief_title>Is Recombinant Growth Hormone Therapy Associated With Increased Intraoccular Pressure?</brief_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>Assaf-Harofeh Medical Center</agency>
      <agency_class>Other</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>Assaf-Harofeh Medical Center</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Recombinant growth hormone is a common therapy in the pediatric population. A number of
      associated side effects have been described. Several years ago, a case report was published
      concerning a child that was treated with RGH and developed acute glaucoma. To date no study
      has evaluated the connection.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
